  "title": "Cybersecurity Trainer",
  "description": "<p>As a Cybersecurity Trainer, you’ll be responsible for conducting quality training to our clients, as well as advising them on the types of training suitable for their employees in order to upgrade their cybersecurity capabilities.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct training for our range of cybersecurity courses</li>\n  <li>Guide students through coursework and projects</li>\n  <li>Contribute to the further development of course materials</li>\n  <li>Conducting cyber ranges for clients</li>\n  <li>Advise clients on suitable types of training to conduct based on the profiles of their employees</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Passing our technical assessment (no minimum academic qualifications or certifications required)</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Python</li>\n  <li>Knowledge in Networking</li>\n  <li>Hands-on experience in one of the following areas: IR, Pentest, OS Internals, Malware Analysis, Threat Hunting, SOC, Cloud Security, Cyber Threat Intelligence</li>\n  <li>Strong presentation skills, written and verbal communication skills</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Desired Qualities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Team player</li>\n  <li>Willingness to pick up new skills</li>\n  <li>Comfortable with engaging large group</li>\n</ul>",
